138 inline bool IsAuraApplyEffects(SpellEntry const* entry, SpellEffectIndexMask mask)
139 {
140  if (!entry)
141  return false;
142  uint32 emptyMask = 0;
143  for (uint32 i = EFFECT_INDEX_0; i < MAX_EFFECT_INDEX; ++i)
144  {
145  const uint32 current = (1 << i);
146  if (entry->Effect[i])
147  {
148  if ((mask & current) && !IsAuraApplyEffect(entry, SpellEffectIndex(i)))
149  return false;
150  }
151  else
152  emptyMask |= current;
153  }
154  // Check if all queried effects are actually empty
155  const bool empty = !(mask & ~emptyMask);
156  return !empty;
157 }

395 inline bool IsSpellEffectAbleToCrit(const SpellEntry* entry, SpellEffectIndex index)
396 {
397  if (!entry || entry->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR_EX2_CANT_CRIT))
398  return false;
399

402  case SPELL_EFFECT_SCHOOL_DAMAGE:

404  case SPELL_EFFECT_WEAPON_DAMAGE_NOSCHOOL:

492 inline uint32 GetAllowedMechanicMask(SpellEntry const* spellProto)
493 {
494  uint32 mask = 0;
495  for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_EFFECT_INDEX; ++i)
496  {
497  if (!spellProto->Effect[i])
498  continue;
499 
500  if (spellProto->EffectApplyAuraName[i] == SPELL_AURA_MECHANIC_IMMUNITY)
501  mask |= 1 << uint32(spellProto->EffectMiscValue[i] - 1);
502  else if (spellProto->EffectApplyAuraName[i] == SPELL_AURA_MECHANIC_IMMUNITY_MASK)
503  mask |= uint32(spellProto->EffectMiscValue[i]);
504  }
505  return mask;
506 }

508 // based on client Spell_C::CancelsAuraEffect
509 inline bool SpellCancelsAuraEffect(SpellEntry const* spellInfo, SpellEntry const* auraSpellInfo, uint8 auraEffIndex)
510 {
511  if (!spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR_EX_IMMUNITY_PURGES_EFFECT))
512  return false;
513 
514  if (auraSpellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR_NO_IMMUNITIES))
515  return false;
516 
517  for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
518  {
519  if (spellInfo->Effect[i] != SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AURA)
520  continue;
521 
522  uint32 const miscValue = static_cast<uint32>(spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[i]);
523  switch (spellInfo->EffectApplyAuraName[i])
524  {
525  case SPELL_AURA_STATE_IMMUNITY:
526  if (miscValue != auraSpellInfo->EffectApplyAuraName[auraEffIndex])
527  continue;
528  break;
529  case SPELL_AURA_SCHOOL_IMMUNITY:
530  if (auraSpellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR_EX2_NO_SCHOOL_IMMUNITIES) || !(auraSpellInfo->SchoolMask & miscValue))
531  continue;
532  break;
533  case SPELL_AURA_DISPEL_IMMUNITY:
534  if (miscValue != auraSpellInfo->Dispel)
535  continue;
536  break;
537  case SPELL_AURA_MECHANIC_IMMUNITY:
538  if (miscValue != auraSpellInfo->Mechanic)
539  if (miscValue != auraSpellInfo->EffectMechanic[auraEffIndex])
540  continue;
541  break;
542  default:
543  continue;
544  }
545 
546  return true;
547  }
548 
549  return false;
550 }

876 inline bool IsSpellEffectDamage(SpellEntry const& spellInfo, SpellEffectIndex i)
877 {
878  if (!spellInfo.EffectApplyAuraName[i])
879  {
880  // If its not an aura effect, check for damage effects
881  switch (spellInfo.Effect[i])
882  {
883  case SPELL_EFFECT_SCHOOL_DAMAGE:
884  case SPELL_EFFECT_ENVIRONMENTAL_DAMAGE:
885  case SPELL_EFFECT_HEALTH_LEECH:
886  case SPELL_EFFECT_WEAPON_DAMAGE_NOSCHOOL:
887  case SPELL_EFFECT_WEAPON_PERCENT_DAMAGE:
888  case SPELL_EFFECT_WEAPON_DAMAGE:
889  // SPELL_EFFECT_POWER_BURN: deals damage for power burned, but its either full damage or resist?
890  case SPELL_EFFECT_NORMALIZED_WEAPON_DMG:
891  return true;
892  }
893  }
894  else
895  {
896  // If its an aura effect, check for DoT auras
897  switch (spellInfo.EffectApplyAuraName[i])
898  {
899  case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_DAMAGE:
900  case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_LEECH:
901  // SPELL_AURA_POWER_BURN_MANA: deals damage for power burned, but not really a DoT?
902  case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_MANA_LEECH: // confirmed via 31447
903  case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_DAMAGE_PERCENT:
904  return true;
905  }
906  }
907  return false;
908 }

932 inline bool IsSpellEffectsDamage(SpellEntry const& spellInfo, uint8 effectMask = EFFECT_MASK_ALL)
933 {

942 inline bool IsBinarySpell(SpellEntry const& spellInfo, uint8 effectMask = EFFECT_MASK_ALL)
943 {
944  // Spell is considered binary if:
945  // * (Pre-WotLK): It contains non-damage effects or auras
946  // * (WotLK+): It contains no damage effects or auras
947  uint8 validmask = 0; // A bitmask of effects: set bits are valid effects
948  uint8 nondmgmask = 0; // A bitmask of effects: set bits are non-damage effects
949  uint8 auramask = 0; // A bitmask of aura effcts: set bits are auras
950  for (uint32 i = EFFECT_INDEX_0; i < MAX_EFFECT_INDEX; ++i)
951  {
952  const uint8 thisMask = uint8(1 << i);
953 
954  if (!spellInfo.Effect[i] || !(effectMask & thisMask))
955  continue;
956 
957  if (IsSpellEffectDummy(spellInfo, SpellEffectIndex(i)) || IsSpellEffectTriggerSpell(&spellInfo, SpellEffectIndex(i)))
958  continue;
959 
960  validmask |= thisMask;
961 
962  if (spellInfo.EffectApplyAuraName[i])
963  auramask |= thisMask;
964  if (!IsSpellEffectDamage(spellInfo, SpellEffectIndex(i)))
965  nondmgmask |= thisMask;
966  }
967  // No valid effects: treat as non-binary
968  if (!validmask)
969  return false;
970  // All effects are non-damage: treat as binary
971  // All effects are auras: treat as binary (even pure DoTs are treated as binary on initial application)
972  if (nondmgmask == validmask || auramask == validmask)
973  return true;
974  const uint8 dmgmask = (validmask & ~nondmgmask);
975  const uint8 dotmask = (dmgmask & auramask);
976  // Just in case, if all damage effects are DoTs: treat as binary
977  if (dmgmask == dotmask)
978  return true;
979  // If we ended up here, we have at least one non-aura damage effect
980  // WotLK+: check if at least one non-damage effect hits the same target as damage effect (e.g. Frostbolt) and treat as binary
981  if (nondmgmask)
982  {
983  uint8 directmask = (dmgmask & ~dotmask);
984  for (uint8 i = EFFECT_INDEX_0; directmask; (++i, (directmask >>= 1)))
985  {
986  if (directmask & 1)
987  {
988  uint8 jmask = nondmgmask;
989  for (uint8 j = EFFECT_INDEX_0; jmask; (++j, (jmask >>= 1)))
990  {
991  if (jmask & 1)
992  {
993  if (spellInfo.EffectImplicitTargetA[i] == spellInfo.EffectImplicitTargetA[j] &&
994  spellInfo.EffectImplicitTargetB[i] == spellInfo.EffectImplicitTargetB[j])
995  {
996  return !(j < i && (auramask & (1 << (j - 1))) && spellInfo.EffectMechanic[j]); // WotLK+: exclude Frostbolt-like structure
997  }
998  }
999  }
1000  }
1001  }
1002  }
1003  return false;
1004 }

1376 inline bool IsPositiveEffectTargetMode(const SpellEntry* entry, SpellEffectIndex effIndex, const WorldObject* caster = nullptr, const WorldObject* target = nullptr, bool recursive = false)
1377 {
1378  if (!entry)
1379  return false;
1380 
1381  // Triggered spells case: prefer child spell via IsPositiveSpell()-like scan for triggered spell
1382  if (IsSpellEffectTriggerSpell(entry, effIndex))
1383  {
1384  const uint32 spellid = entry->EffectTriggerSpell[effIndex];
1385  // Its possible to go infinite cycle with triggered spells. We are interested to peek only at the first layer so far
1386  if (!recursive && spellid && (spellid != entry->Id))
1387  {
1388  if (const SpellEntry* triggered = sSpellTemplate.LookupEntry<SpellEntry>(spellid))
1389  {
1390  for (uint32 i = EFFECT_INDEX_0; i < MAX_EFFECT_INDEX; ++i)
1391  {
1392  if (!IsPositiveEffectTargetMode(triggered, SpellEffectIndex(i), caster, target, true))
1393  return false;
1394  }
1395  }
1396  }
1397  // For trigger effects target modes are inconsistent: we have invalid and coflicting ones
1398  // Let's try to ignore them completely
1399  return true;
1400  }
1401 
1402  const uint32 a = entry->EffectImplicitTargetA[effIndex];
1403  const uint32 b = entry->EffectImplicitTargetB[effIndex];
1404 
1405  if ((!a && !b) || IsEffectTargetPositive(a, b) || IsEffectTargetScript(a, b))
1406  return true;
1407  if (IsEffectTargetNegative(a, b))
1408  {
1409  // Workaround: Passive talents with negative target modes are getting removed by ice block and similar effects
1410  // TODO: Fix removal of passives in appropriate places and remove the check below afterwards
1411  return entry->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR_PASSIVE);
1412  }
1413  if (IsEffectTargetNeutral(a, b))
1414  return (IsPointEffectTarget(SpellTarget(b ? b : a)) || IsNeutralEffectTargetPositive((b ? b : a), caster, target));
1415 
1416  // If we ever get to this point, we have unhandled target. Gotta say something about it.
1417  if (entry->Effect[effIndex])
1418  DETAIL_LOG("IsPositiveEffectTargetMode: Spell %u's effect %u has unhandled targets (A:%u B:%u)", entry->Id, effIndex,
1419  entry->EffectImplicitTargetA[effIndex], entry->EffectImplicitTargetB[effIndex]);
1420  return true;
1421 }

1700  {

1702  if (auraSpellInfo->Mechanic != MECHANIC_IMMUNE_SHIELD &&
1703  auraSpellInfo->Mechanic != MECHANIC_INVULNERABILITY &&
1704  auraSpellInfo->Mechanic != MECHANIC_BANISH)
1705  return true;
1706  }
1707 
1708  if (spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR_EX_IMMUNITY_PURGES_EFFECT))
1709  {
1710  for (int i = 0; i < MAX_EFFECT_INDEX; ++i)
1711  {
1712  uint32 miscValue = (uint32)spellInfo->EffectMiscValue[i];
1713  if (spellInfo->Effect[i] && spellInfo->EffectApplyAuraName[i] == SPELL_AURA_MECHANIC_IMMUNITY_MASK)
1714  if (effectMask & (1 << i))
1715  if (miscValue & (1 << auraSpellInfo->Mechanic) || miscValue & (1 << auraSpellInfo->EffectMechanic[effIdx]))
1716  return true;
1717  }
1718  }
1719 
1720  // TODO: Add SPELL_ATTR_EX_DISPEL_AURAS_ON_IMMUNITY logic
1721 
1722  return false;
1723 }

2065 inline bool IsStackableAuraEffect(SpellEntry const* entry, SpellEntry const* entry2, uint32 i, Unit* pTarget = nullptr)
2066 {
2067  const uint32 aura = entry->EffectApplyAuraName[i];
2068  // Ignore non-aura effects
2069  if (!aura)
2070  return true;
2071 
2072  // Get first similar - second spell's same aura with the same sign
2073  uint32 similar = EFFECT_INDEX_0;
2074  for (uint32 e = EFFECT_INDEX_0; e < MAX_EFFECT_INDEX; ++e)
2075  {
2076  if (IsSimilarAuraEffect(entry, i, entry2, e))
2077  {
2078  similar = e;
2079  break;
2080  }
2081  else if (e == (MAX_EFFECT_INDEX - 1))
2082  return true; // No similarities
2083  }
2084 
2085  // Special case for potions
2086  if (entry->SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_POTION || entry2->SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_POTION)
2087  return true;
2088 
2089  // Special rule for food buffs
2090  if (GetSpellSpecific(entry->Id) == SPELL_WELL_FED && GetSpellSpecific(entry2->Id) != SPELL_WELL_FED)
2091  return true;
2092 
2093  // Short alias
2094  const bool positive = (IsPositiveEffect(entry, SpellEffectIndex(i)));
2095  const bool related = (entry->SpellFamilyName == entry2->SpellFamilyName);
2096  const bool siblings = (entry->SpellFamilyFlags == entry2->SpellFamilyFlags);
2097  const bool player = (entry->SpellFamilyName && !entry->SpellFamilyFlags.Empty());
2098  const bool multirank = (related && siblings && player);
2099  const bool instance = (entry->Id == entry2->Id || multirank);
2100  const bool icon = (entry->SpellIconID == entry2->SpellIconID); // Old bad practice, but a few old spells detection may still depend on it
2101  const bool visual = (entry->SpellVisual[0] == entry2->SpellVisual[0]); // Old bad practice, but a few old spells detection may still depend on it
2102 
2103  // If aura makes spell not multi-instanceable (do not stack the same spell id or ranks of this spell)
2104  bool nonmui = false;
2105 
2106  // Stack rules
2107  switch (aura)
2108  {
2109  // Dummy/Triggers
2110  case SPELL_AURA_DUMMY:
2111  case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_DUMMY:
2112  case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_TRIGGER_SPELL:
2113  {
2114  if (!related)
2115  break;
2116  switch (entry->SpellFamilyName)
2117  {
2118  case SPELLFAMILY_GENERIC:
2119  if (entry->SpellIconID == 92 && entry->SpellVisual[0] == 99 && icon && visual)
2120  return false; // Soulstone Resurrection
2121  if (entry->Id == 31944) // Archimonde - Doomfire
2122  return false;
2123  break;
2124  case SPELLFAMILY_SHAMAN:
2125  if (entry->IsFitToFamilyMask(uint64(0x200)) && multirank)
2126  return true; // Shaman Reincarnation (Passive) and Twisting Nether
2127  break;
2128  case SPELLFAMILY_DRUID:
2129  if (entry->IsFitToFamilyMask(uint64(0x44000000000)) && entry2->IsFitToFamilyMask(uint64(0x44000000000)))
2130  return false; // Mangle (Cat) & Mangle (Bear)
2131  if (entry->IsFitToFamilyMask(uint64(0x80)) && multirank)
2132  return true; // Tranquility
2133  if (entry->IsFitToFamilyMask(uint64(0x01000000000)))
2134  return true; // Lifebloom
2135  break;
2136  }
2137  break;
2138  }
2139  // DoT
2140  case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_LEECH:
2141  case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_MANA_LEECH:
2142  if (pTarget && pTarget->HasFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_PLAYER_CONTROLLED))
2143  return false;
2144  break;
2145  case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_DAMAGE:
2146  case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_DAMAGE_PERCENT:
2147  case SPELL_AURA_POWER_BURN_MANA:
2148  if (entry->Id == 38575) // Vashj - Toxic Spores
2149  return false;
2150  if (entry->Id == 45402) // Felmyst - Demonic Vapor
2151  return false;
2152  if (entry->Id == 45032 || entry->Id == 45034) // Kalecgos - Curse of boundless agony
2153  if (entry2->Id == 45032 || entry2->Id == 45034)
2154  return false;
2155  return true;
2156  break;
2157  // HoT
2158  case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_HEAL:
2159  case SPELL_AURA_OBS_MOD_HEALTH:
2160  case SPELL_AURA_OBS_MOD_MANA:
2161  return true;
2162  break;
2163  // Raid debuffs: Hunter's Mark and Expose Weakness stack with each other, but not itself
2164  case SPELL_AURA_RANGED_ATTACK_POWER_ATTACKER_BONUS:
2165  case SPELL_AURA_MELEE_ATTACK_POWER_ATTACKER_BONUS:
2166  return (!related || !siblings);
2167  break;
2168  case SPELL_AURA_MOD_ATTACK_POWER:
2169  // Attack Power debuffs logic: Do not stack Curse of Weakness, Demoralizing Roars/Shouts
2170  if (!positive && entry->EffectBasePoints[i] < 1 && entry2->EffectBasePoints[similar] < 1)
2171  return (!entry->SpellFamilyName && !entry2->SpellFamilyName);
2172  break;
2173  // Armor & Resistance buffs and debuffs logic
2174  case SPELL_AURA_MOD_RESISTANCE:
2175  {
2176  if (entry->EffectMiscValue[i] != entry2->EffectMiscValue[similar])
2177  break;
2178  if (positive)
2179  {
2180  // Used as a non-zero type in this context
2181  const bool type = (entry->Dispel && entry->Dispel == entry2->Dispel);
2182  const bool attacktable = (entry->DmgClass && entry->DmgClass == entry2->DmgClass);
2183  if ((attacktable || type) && !entry->SpellFamilyName && !entry2->SpellFamilyName)
2184  return false; // Do not stack scrolls with other srolls and some procs (such as Hyjal ring)
2185  if (player && related && siblings && entry->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR_EX3_DOT_STACKING_RULE))
2186  return true;
2187  }
2188  else
2189  {
2190  const bool type = (entry->Dispel == entry2->Dispel);
2191  const bool prevention = (entry->PreventionType && entry->PreventionType == entry2->PreventionType);
2192  if (type && prevention)
2193  return false;
2194  }
2195  break;
2196  }
2197  case SPELL_AURA_MOD_RESISTANCE_PCT:
2198  {
2199  if (entry->EffectMiscValue[i] != entry2->EffectMiscValue[similar])
2200  break;
2201  if (positive && entry->Dispel && entry->Dispel == entry2->Dispel)
2202  return false; // Inspiration / Ancestral Fortitude
2203  nonmui = true;
2204  break;
2205  }
2206  // By default base stats cannot stack if they're similar
2207  case SPELL_AURA_MOD_STAT:
2208  {
2209  if (entry->Id == 8733 && entry2->Id == 8733) // Blessing of Blackfathom - shouldnt stack with itself
2210  return false;
2211  if (entry->Id == 5320 || entry2->Id == 5320) // Echeyakee's Grace - stacks with everything
2212  return true;
2213  if (entry->Id == 15366 || entry2->Id == 15366) // Songflower Serenade - stacks with everything
2214  return true;
2215  if (entry->Id == 24425 && entry2->Id == 24425) // Spirit of Zandalar - shouldnt stack with itself
2216  return false;
2217  if (entry->EffectMiscValue[i] != entry2->EffectMiscValue[similar])
2218  break;
2219  if (positive)
2220  {
2221  // Used as a non-zero type in this context
2222  const bool type = (entry->Dispel && entry->Dispel == entry2->Dispel);
2223  const bool family = (entry->SpellFamilyName || entry2->SpellFamilyName);
2224  const bool uncategorized = (!entry->SpellFamilyName || !entry2->SpellFamilyName);
2225  if (type && family && uncategorized)
2226  return false; // Do not stack player buffs with scrolls
2227  if (!entry->SpellFamilyName && !entry2->SpellFamilyName)
2228  {
2229  if (type)
2230  return false; // Do not stack scrolls and other non-player buffs with each other
2231  if (entry->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR_EX2_NOT_AN_ACTION) && entry2->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR_EX2_NOT_AN_ACTION))
2232  return false; // FIXME: Cozy fire hack
2233  }
2234  }
2235  else
2236  {
2237  // Debuffs are based on patch notes decription of Shrink effects stacking
2238  // Used as a non-zero type in this context
2239  const bool type = (entry->Dispel && entry->Dispel == entry2->Dispel);
2240  if (type)
2241  return false;
2242  nonmui = true;
2243  }
2244  break;
2245  }
2246  case SPELL_AURA_MOD_TOTAL_STAT_PERCENTAGE:
2247  case SPELL_AURA_MOD_PERCENT_STAT:
2248  nonmui = true;
2249  break;
2250  case SPELL_AURA_MOD_INCREASE_HEALTH:
2251  if (entry->Id == 26522 && entry2->Id == 26522) // Lunar Fortune
2252  return false;
2253  break;
2254  case SPELL_AURA_MOD_HEALING_DONE:
2255  case SPELL_AURA_MOD_HEALING_PCT:
2256  // Do not stack similar debuffs: Mortal Strike, Aimed Shot, Hex of Weakness
2257  if (!positive)
2258  return (entry->EffectMiscValue[i] == entry2->EffectMiscValue[similar]);
2259  break;
2260  case SPELL_AURA_MOD_MELEE_HASTE:
2261  case SPELL_AURA_MOD_RANGED_HASTE:
2262  case SPELL_AURA_MOD_DAMAGE_DONE:
2263  case SPELL_AURA_MOD_DAMAGE_PERCENT_DONE: // Ferocious Inspiration, Shadow Embrace
2264  if (entry->Id == 29521 && entry2->Id == 29521) // Dance Vibe
2265  return false;
2266  if (positive)
2267  return true;
2268  nonmui = true;
2269  break;
2270  case SPELL_AURA_MOD_SPELL_CRIT_CHANCE:
2271  case SPELL_AURA_MOD_SPELL_HIT_CHANCE:
2272  case SPELL_AURA_MOD_DAMAGE_TAKEN:
2273  case SPELL_AURA_MOD_DAMAGE_PERCENT_TAKEN:
2274  case SPELL_AURA_MOD_DECREASE_SPEED: // Bonus stacking handled by core
2275  case SPELL_AURA_MOD_INCREASE_SPEED: // Bonus stacking handled by core
2276  case SPELL_AURA_MOD_HEALTH_REGEN_PERCENT:
2277  case SPELL_AURA_PREVENTS_FLEEING:
2278  nonmui = true;
2279  break;
2280  case SPELL_AURA_PROC_TRIGGER_SPELL:
2281  if (instance && !icon)
2282  // Exception: Judgement of Light and Judgement of Wisdom have exact same spell family flags
2283  // Comparing icons is the fastest (but hacky) way to destinguish between two without poking spell chain
2284  break;
2285  nonmui = true;
2286  break;
2287  case SPELL_AURA_MOD_RATING: // Whitelisted, Rejuvenation has this
2288  case SPELL_AURA_SPELL_MAGNET: // Party auras whitelist for Grounding Totem
2289  return true; // Always stacking auras
2290  break;
2291  case SPELL_AURA_MOD_POSSESS: // Mind control derrivatives
2292  case SPELL_AURA_MOD_POSSESS_PET: // Eyes of the beast
2293  case SPELL_AURA_MOD_CHARM: // Temporary Enslave/Tame derrivatives
2294  case SPELL_AURA_AOE_CHARM: // Mass charm by Boss/NPC
2295  case SPELL_AURA_DAMAGE_SHIELD: // Damage shields: Fire Shield, Thorns...
2296  case SPELL_AURA_MOD_SHAPESHIFT: // Forms and stances
2297  case SPELL_AURA_MOUNTED: // Mount
2298  case SPELL_AURA_EMPATHY: // Beast Lore
2299  case SPELL_AURA_PHASE:
2300  case SPELL_AURA_SET_VEHICLE_ID: // Enable Vehicle template on players or other non vehicle units
2301  // TODO: Make these exclusive rather than unstackable physically and move to nonmui:
2302  case SPELL_AURA_MOD_CASTING_SPEED_NOT_STACK: // Heroism, Bloodlust, Icy Veins, Power Infusion
2303  case SPELL_AURA_MOD_MOUNTED_SPEED_NOT_STACK: // Mounted Speed effects
2304  case SPELL_AURA_HASTE_SPELLS: // Post 2.0 Mind-numbing Poison and Curse of Tongues
2305  return false; // Never stacking auras
2306  break;
2307  case SPELL_AURA_MOD_DETECT_RANGE: // Never stack
2308  return false;
2309  case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_ENERGIZE:
2310  if (entry->Id == 45860 && entry2->Id == 45860) // Breath: Revitalize
2311  return false;
2312  break;
2313  }
2314  if (nonmui && instance && !IsChanneledSpell(entry) && !IsChanneledSpell(entry2))
2315  return false; // Forbids multi-ranking and multi-application on rule, exclude channeled spells (like Mind Flay)
2316 
2317  if (multirank && IsPositiveSpell(entry) && IsPositiveSpell(entry2))
2318  return false; // Forbids multi-ranking for positive spells
2319 
2320  return true;
2321 }

2323 inline bool IsStackableSpell(SpellEntry const* entry, SpellEntry const* entry2, Unit* pTarget = nullptr)
2324 {
2325  for (uint32 i = EFFECT_INDEX_0; i < MAX_EFFECT_INDEX; ++i)
2326  {
2327  if (entry->Effect[i] && entry->EffectApplyAuraName[i] && !IsStackableAuraEffect(entry, entry2, i, pTarget))

2333 inline bool IsSimilarExistingAuraStronger(const SpellAuraHolder* holder, const SpellAuraHolder* existing)
2334 {
2335  if (!holder || !existing)
2336  return false;
2337  const SpellEntry* entry = holder->GetSpellProto();
2338  const SpellEntry* entry2 = existing->GetSpellProto();
2339  if (!entry || !entry2)
2340  return false;
2341 
2342  // Already compared effects masks to avoid re-entrance
2343  uint32 effectmask1 = 0;
2344  uint32 effectmask2 = 0;
2345 
2346  for (uint32 e = EFFECT_INDEX_0; e < MAX_EFFECT_INDEX; ++e)
2347  {
2348  for (uint32 e2 = EFFECT_INDEX_0; e2 < MAX_EFFECT_INDEX; ++e2)
2349  {
2350  if (IsSimilarAuraEffect(entry, e, entry2, e2) && !(effectmask1 & (1 << e)) && !(effectmask2 & (1 << e2)))
2351  {
2352  effectmask1 |= (1 << e);
2353  effectmask2 |= (1 << e2);
2354  Aura* aura1 = holder->GetAuraByEffectIndex(SpellEffectIndex(e));
2355  Aura* aura2 = existing->GetAuraByEffectIndex(SpellEffectIndex(e2));
2356  int32 value = aura1 ? (aura1->GetModifier()->m_amount / int32(aura1->GetStackAmount())) : 0;
2357  int32 value2 = aura2 ? (aura2->GetModifier()->m_amount / int32(aura2->GetStackAmount())) : 0;
2358  if (value < 0 && value2 < 0)
2359  {
2360  value = abs(value);
2361  value2 = abs(value2);
2362  }
2363  if (value2 > value)
2364  return true;
2365  }
2366  }
2367  }
2368  return false;
2369 }

2371 inline bool IsSimilarExistingAuraStronger(const Unit* caster, const SpellEntry* entry, const SpellAuraHolder* existing, uint32 affectedMask, int32 amounts[MAX_EFFECT_INDEX])

2374  return false;

2376  if (!entry || !entry2)
2377  return false;

2381  uint32 effectmask2 = 0;
2382

2384  {

2386  {

2390  {
2391  effectmask1 |= (1 << e);
2392  effectmask2 |= (1 << e2);
2393  Aura* aura = existing->GetAuraByEffectIndex(SpellEffectIndex(e2));
2394  int32 value = amounts[e];
2395  int32 value2 = aura ? (aura->GetModifier()->m_amount / int32(aura->GetStackAmount())) : 0;
2396  if (value < 0 && value2 < 0)
2397  {
2398  value = abs(value);
2399  value2 = abs(value2);
2400  }
2401  if (value2 > value)
2402  return true;
2403  }
2404  }
2405  }
2406  }
2407  return false;
